By Mark Corti

We've added a new date for our beginner courses, and still have a few spaces left!  The course will run on Monday evenings, starting next Monday (19th).  Get in quick before they're all gone!

Click here to see details and book your space.

New Newsletter!

Details
By Mark Corti

The next edition of the newsletter is out soon, so if you've been doing any paddling over the summer, or have some news / opinions / whatever you want to share, please send it over to newsletter@maidstonecanoeclub.net by the 10th August!

Canoe Club Security

Details
By Mark Corti

The Club is not being locked up properly when people leave.  It was left unlocked again last night.  The magnetic locks are not sufficient to make the Club secure - the padlocks & locks must be locked also.  We are not insured if you do not.

Please don't assume that someone else is going to lock up - double-check or do it yourself!

Herne Beach Social - not at Herne Beach!

Details
By Mark Corti

Note new location: Hythe!  Please see the forum for details.

A few Club members, organised by Richard, are heading down to Hythe  next weekend for a family barbecue & paddle - take a look at the forum for details.

New Introductory Course Dates

Details
By Mark Corti

We've still got spaces left on our new Friday-night Intro Course, starting on August 9th.  If you fancy learning to paddle, this is the place to start!  There's more about what's involved here, as well as details of our new course dates in September.

Gutless Kayaking

Details
By Mark Corti

Local paddler Justin Hansen, aka the Gutless Kayaker, is undertaking a World-Record-Breaking 420-mile sponsored paddle from Skipton to Bristol later this year, sponsored by everyone's favourite kayak shop, Kent Canoes.  Why is this record breaking?  Because Justin's paddling without most of his bowels.  This means he will be connected to a kind of portable life-support machine every day while he paddles, and every night while he sleeps.  Take a look at his inspirational fundraising journeys on his website.
